  "text": "Django's model field validation system is implemented across multiple modules, with a comprehensive pipeline for validating data at multiple levels.\n\n**Core Validators (django/core/validators.py):** The foundation consists of validator classes like RegexValidator, EmailValidator, URLValidator, and a hierarchy of constraint validators built on BaseValidator (MaxValueValidator, MinValueValidator, MinLengthValidator, MaxLengthValidator, StepValueValidator, DecimalValidator, FileExtensionValidator, ProhibitNullCharactersValidator, and DomainNameValidator). These are used throughout Django's form and model systems.\n\n**Model Field Validation Chain:** In django/db/models/fields/__init__.py, the Field class implements three key methods:\n- validate() method (line 798-827): Performs field-specific validation including choice validation, null/blank checking\n- run_validators() method (line 782-796): Executes all validators attached to the field\n- clean() method (line 829-838): Orchestrates the full validation by calling to_python(), validate(), and run_validators() in sequence\n\n**Model-Level Validation (django/db/models/base.py):** The Model class implements a four-step validation pipeline:\n- full_clean() method (line 1690-1735): Orchestrates all validation steps including clean_fields(), clean(), validate_unique(), and validate_constraints()\n- clean_fields() method (line 1737-1763): Validates individual model fields by calling Field.clean() on each field\n- clean() hook method: User-defined validation logic hook\n- validate_unique() method (line 1450-1467): Validates unique constraints and unique_for_date/time constraints\n- validate_constraints() method (line 1670-1688): Validates CheckConstraint and UniqueConstraint instances\n\n**Constraint Validation (django/db/models/constraints.py):** The BaseConstraint class and its subclasses (CheckConstraint, UniqueConstraint) implement a validate() method that is called during Model.validate_constraints(). These constraints can be conditional using Q expressions and handle database-level constraint validation.\n\n**Form Field Validation (django/forms/fields.py):** The Form Field class mirrors the model field validation:\n- clean() method (line 202-210): Validates by calling to_python(), validate(), and run_validators()\n- to_python() method (line 181-182): Type conversion\n- validate() method (line 184-186): Required field validation\n- run_validators() method (line 188-200): Executes all field validators\n\n**Form-Level Validation (django/forms/forms.py):** BaseForm implements:\n- full_clean() method (line 324-339): Coordinates _clean_fields(), _clean_form(), and _post_clean()\n- _clean_fields() method (line 341-350): Validates individual fields\n- _clean_form() method (line 352-359): Calls the clean() hook\n- clean() hook method (line 368-375): User-defined validation\n\n**ModelForm Integration (django/forms/models.py):** The ModelForm._post_clean() method (line 361-505) bridges form and model validation by calling instance.full_clean() with appropriate exclusions for validate_unique and validate_constraints.\n\n**PostgreSQL Extensions (django/contrib/postgres/):** PostgreSQL-specific validators in validators.py include ArrayMaxLengthValidator, ArrayMinLengthValidator, RangeMaxValueValidator, and RangeMinValueValidator. The constraints.py module provides ExclusionConstraint.validate() for PostgreSQL exclusion constraints. Array fields in fields/array.py and hstore fields override validate() and run_validators() methods.\n\n**Authentication Validators (django/contrib/auth/validators.py):** Specialized validators ASCIIUsernameValidator and UnicodeUsernameValidator extend RegexValidator for username validation.\n\n**Formset Validation (django/forms/formsets.py):** BaseFormSet.full_clean() method (line 396-414) validates each form in the formset and enforces formset-level uniqueness constraints.\n\nThe validation flow is hierarchical: Model.full_clean() → clean_fields() → Field.clean() → validate() → run_validators() → BaseValidator subclasses. For forms: Form.full_clean() → _clean_fields() → Field.clean() → validate() → run_validators() → validator instances. ModelForm bridges both by calling Model.full_clean() in _post_clean() after form validation."
