  "text": "Django's model field validation system is implemented across multiple modules, with a comprehensive pipeline for validating data at multiple levels.\n\n**Core Validators (django/core/validators.py):** The foundation consists of validator classes like RegexValidator, EmailValidator, URLValidator, and a hierarchy of constraint validators built on BaseValidator (MaxValueValidator, MinValueValidator, MinLengthValidator, MaxLengthValidator, StepValueValidator, DecimalValidator, FileExtensionValidator, ProhibitNullCharactersValidator, and DomainNameValidator). These are used throughout Django's form and model systems.\n\n**Model Field Validation Chain:** In django/db/models/fields/__init__.py, the Field class implements three key methods:\n- validate() method (line 798-827): Performs field-specific validation including choice validation, null/blank checking\n- run_validators() method (line 782-796): Executes all validators attached to the field\n- clean() method (line 829-838): Orchestrates the full validation by calling to_python(), validate(), and run_validators() in sequence\n\n**Model-Level Validation (django/db/models/base.py):** The Model class implements a four-step validation pipeline:\n- full_clean() method (line 1690-1735): Orchestrates all validation steps including clean_fields(), clean(), validate_unique(), and validate_constraints()\n- clean_fields() method (line 1737-1763): Validates individual model fields by calling Field.clean() on each field\n- clean() hook method: User-defined validation logic hook\n- validate_unique() method (line 1450-1467): Validates unique constraints and unique_for_date/time constraints\n- validate_constraints() method (line 1670-1688): Validates CheckConstraint and UniqueConstraint instances\n\n**Constraint Validation (django/db/models/constraints.py):** The BaseConstraint class and its subclasses (CheckConstraint, UniqueConstraint) implement a validate() method that is called during Model.validate_constraints(). These